---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Cookie Policy | freellm.site"
  description="Cookie policy for freellm.site — what cookies we use, why, and how to manage your preferences."
>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: June 28, 2026</p>
    <p class="legal-lead">
      This page explains how freellm.site uses cookies and similar technologies, and how you can control them.
    </p>

    <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help sites remember preferences, measure traffic, and serve relevant content or ads.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies we use</h2>

    <h3>Essential cookies</h3>
    <p>These are required for basic site functionality, such as remembering your cookie consent choice. They cannot be disabled.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>freellm-cookie-consent</strong> — stores your cookie preference (localStorage, not a traditional cookie)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Analytics cookies</h3>
    <p>Used to understand how visitors interact with the site. Only set if you accept all cookies.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — _ga, _ga_* and related identifiers. See <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/cookies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's cookie documentation</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Advertising cookies</h3>
    <p>Used to serve and measure ads. Only set if you accept all cookies.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — cookies such as __gads, __gpi, and partner cookies. See <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google advertising cookies</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Managing your preferences</h2>
    <p>When you first visit freellm.site, a banner lets you choose:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Accept all</strong> — enables analytics and advertising cookies</li>
      <li><strong>Essential only</strong> — disables analytics and advertising cookies</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To change your choice, clear site data for freellm.site in your browser settings and revisit the site.</p>
    <p>You can also opt out of personalized ads at <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>.</p>

    <h2>Third-party cookies</h2>
    <p>Google and its advertising partners may set cookies when you visit pages with AdSense units. We do not control these cookies directly.</p>

    <h2>More information</h2>
    <p>For how we handle personal data, see our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>. Questions? Visit our <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
